                            <comment id="17482963" author="JIRAUSER284274" created="Thu, 27 Jan 2022 08:28:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A similar issue was solved in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-21567&quot; title=&quot;Dataset with Tuple of type alias throws error&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-21567&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-21567&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17484506" author="apachespark" created="Mon, 31 Jan 2022 05:15:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;jtnystrom&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/35370&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/35370&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17489167" author="JIRAUSER284274" created="Tue, 8 Feb 2022 23:49:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My initial idea above was wrong. I ended up changing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
val TypeRef(_, _, Seq(elementType)) = tpe&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
val TypeRef(_, _, Seq(elementType)) = tpe.dealias&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and this seems to work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
